        "valid_until": { "$ref": "#/$defs/timestamp" },
        "generated_at": { "$ref": "#/$defs/timestamp" }
      },
      "$comment": "Only the protected reusable verifier may emit a qualifying passed decision. It reconstructs every producer/stage/approval input from bounded current-run IDs and GitHub API state, binds each input manifest ID to its canonical artifact member and re-hashed bytes, verifies attestations, and reads the current protected exception-ledger head/tree through the same-repository API. It rejects a stale or concurrently moved head, schema-validates debt and resolution records, re-hashes every normalized entry into exception_ledger_snapshot_sha256, proves current approvals' registered entries are present and all unresolved historical debt is either passed and registered as resolved now or remains blocking, and prevents an old resolution from satisfying a later distinct debt. It runs policy and coverage code from its independently pinned signer digest rather than the candidate checkout, sets valid_until no later than the earliest current approval expiry (and to a bounded protected-policy lifetime when there is no exception), hashes the exact evidence-set and coverage outputs, and attests this manifest. Repository rules require the installed protected workflow identity, not a name-only status. A caller aggregate, candidate validator, same-name job, UUID-only list, stale ledger snapshot, expired decision, or self-declared success cannot substitute for it."
    }
  }
